main event: A civilian reported seeing one white object the size of a dime remaining stationary for two minutes in Red Oak, Georgia in 1957.
interesting points: The object was observed at a 30 degree elevation.
The sighting lasted for two minutes, providing a relatively long observation time.
The conclusion on the report questions why the object could not be a parachute, indicating a thorough consideration of potential explanations.
Scientific data and obvious analysis were rejected, adding to the mystery of the sighting.
The report does not contain any further scientific or investigative data.
sighted object: one white object the size of a dime
